list (like Perl's @code{for (@@a) @{@dots{}@}}, or Python's @code{for i in aList:
@dots{}}), with Ruby you'll very often instead see:

@example
some_list.each do |this_item|
  # We're inside the block.
  # deal with this_item.
end
@end example

For more info on @code{each} and its friends
